{
  "answer": "**Yājñavalkya Smṛti 1.4–5 lists exactly twenty promulgators (prayojakāḥ) of the Dharmaśāstras, spanning two verses:**\n\n> [p-0f4ad0] Manu, Atri, Viṣṇu, Hārīta, Yājñavalkya, Uśanas, Aṅgiras,  \n> Yama, Āpastamba, Saṃvarta, Kātyāyana, and Bṛhaspati, // Yj_1.4 //[^1]  \n>   \n> [p-95ef53] Parāśara, Vyāsa, Śaṅkha, Likhita, Dakṣa, and Gautama,  \n> Śātātapa, and Vasiṣṭha are the promulgators of the Dharmaśāstras. // Yj_1.5 //[^2]\n\n[^1]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, [p-0f4ad0](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-0f4ad0).\n[^2]: Yājñavalkya Smṛti, [p-95ef53](/works/unknown-yajnavalkya-smrti-cb88d6/01/translation/#p-95ef53).",
